34:19.600 --> 34:21.000
That's a pass.

34:24.000 --> 34:25.400
Alan…

34:25.500 --> 34:28.960
My client has expressed an interest
in working this out.

34:29.000 --> 34:31.760
–That's a pass, too.
–Don't you want to hear a number?

34:31.800 --> 34:33.978
I don't need to hear your number.

34:34.500 --> 34:37.500
–Excuse me. Jury has a verdict.
–Already?

34:39.000 --> 34:40.782
Let's go hear their number.

34:52.400 --> 34:54.260
Maybe we should at least listen
to what they have to say.

34:54.300 --> 34:57.200
It's not too late.
–Yes, it is, for them.

34:57.900 --> 34:58.500
Bethany—–

34:58.600 --> 35:00.660
Mr Foreman, the jury
has reached a verdict?

35:00.700 --> 35:03.500
–We have, your honor.
–What say you?

35:04.900 --> 35:07.860
In the matter of Rhodes vs
A. B. Curtis tobacco company,

35:07.900 --> 35:09.560
on the count of wrongful death,

35:09.600 --> 35:13.100
we find in favor of the plaintiff.

35:13.300 --> 35:14.300
Hot damn!

35:14.400 --> 35:19.560
And we order the defendant to pay
compensatory damages in the amount of $600,000.

35:19.600 --> 35:23.060
We further order the defendant
to pay punitive damages

35:23.100 --> 35:27.200
in the amount of $213 million.

35:27.500 --> 35:28.400
What?

35:29.800 --> 35:32.060
Defense moves for a judgment
notwithstanding the verdict.

35:32.100 --> 35:33.000
Denied.

35:33.200 --> 35:35.360
Defense moves
to set aside the award as excessive.

35:35.400 --> 35:37.900
–Denied.
–We appeal.

35:38.000 --> 35:41.894
So noted. Members of the jury,
this completes your service.

35:42.000 --> 35:44.660
The, uh, court dismisses you
with their thanks,

35:44.700 --> 35:46.900
and we are adjourned.

35:49.000 --> 35:51.508
You gotta feel like getting naked now.

35:53.600 --> 35:54.700
Mr Shore…

35:56.000 --> 35:58.640
I don't know what to say.
–Neither do I.

35:59.300 --> 36:02.300
Alan… thank you so, so much.

36:03.300 --> 36:05.600
Alan, uh, a second, please…

36:06.100 --> 36:07.200
In private?

36:15.400 --> 36:18.400
Well… congratulations.

36:19.800 --> 36:21.060
Obviously, we'll be fighting this.

36:21.100 --> 36:26.000
It'll be years and years before
this thing is remotely over.

36:26.200 --> 36:29.632
I've got time. It's not as
if I'm dying or anything.

36:30.300 --> 36:33.300
No, you're… quite not.

36:38.100 --> 36:39.900
Well, I, um…

36:40.400 --> 36:43.100
I don't do appellate work,

36:43.300 --> 36:45.760
so'll be passing
this on to another lawyer…

36:45.800 --> 36:47.100
So…

36:48.700 --> 36:50.680
I guess this is good-bye then.

36:52.300 --> 36:53.900
Yes.

36:59.300 --> 37:00.700
Well…

37:08.600 --> 37:10.100
Good-bye, Alan.

37:25.100 --> 37:26.400
Good-bye.

37:40.300 --> 37:41.700
You still have me.

37:43.200 --> 37:44.784
It's not quite the same.

37:45.400 --> 37:46.660
But you know what, Denny?

37:46.700 --> 37:50.200
Sometimes it comes remarkably close.

37:51.200 --> 37:55.500
What you said to me
about being undead in the courtroom,

37:55.600 --> 37:57.000
it…

37:59.500 --> 38:01.060
It's not lost on me how lucky I am

38:01.100 --> 38:03.476
to have somebody in my life who can…

38:06.400 --> 38:08.842
I don't know what I'd do without you.

38:19.500 --> 38:21.200
Ahh.

38:22.100 --> 38:23.960
You know, as much
as I hate cigarettes,

38:24.000 --> 38:26.900
I so miss the cigarette break—

38:27.700 --> 38:32.200
A little respite where coworkers would
go outside and be communal,

38:32.300 --> 38:37.000
discuss the trivial annoyances
and affections in their lives

38:37.200 --> 38:40.500
that always turned out
to be anything but trivial.

38:41.900 --> 38:44.474
And to think, I might not
even know you

38:45.400 --> 38:49.060
but for the fact that we both like
to smoke these smelly cancer sticks

38:49.100 --> 38:51.600
that can only be smoked outside.

38:53.300 --> 38:54.800
Hmm.

38:55.200 --> 38:56.784
That would be a tragedy.

38:58.600 --> 39:01.438
I especially can't imagine
being alone now…

39:02.000 --> 39:05.000
when my junk has Alzheimer's.
–Denny.

39:05.000 --> 39:07.660
Well, it's a symptom.
You said so yourself.

39:07.700 --> 39:08.900
It figures.

39:09.000 --> 39:12.300
For me, it would be
the first thing to go.

39:13.700 --> 39:14.600
What's that?

39:14.700 --> 39:19.500
What? Oh. I didn't see it.

39:29.000 --> 39:31.100
Ohh.

39:32.500 --> 39:33.700
Is that the—

39:33.900 --> 39:34.900
it—

39:35.600 --> 39:37.100
N—
–See ya.

39:37.600 --> 39:40.306
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
At least let me see it.

39:49.300 --> 39:50.900
Oh, my.

39:52.300 --> 39:54.742
It's a two-piece, Denny. A share toy.

39:54.800 --> 39:55.960
–Forget it.
–Come on.

39:56.000 --> 39:58.360
–It was a gift to me.
–You take top. I'll take bottom.

39:58.400 --> 40:00.500
Not a chance. Ooh.

40:01.100 --> 40:02.100
What?

40:02.200 --> 40:05.400
I'm cured. I'm back. I'm gone.

40:05.500 --> 40:06.560
Whoawhoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

40:06.600 --> 40:09.600
Why not savor this moment?

40:09.800 --> 40:11.660
At my age, I'm lucky to last a moment.

40:11.700 --> 40:13.660
You take the top, I'll take the bottom.

40:13.700 --> 40:15.160
Tomorrow we'll switch off.

40:15.200 --> 40:17.660
It'll be just like the 3-way
you've always wanted.

40:17.700 --> 40:20.076
I never wanted you as part of the 3.

40:20.600 --> 40:21.900
Denny…

40:22.800 --> 40:25.200
I have never asked you for anything.

40:25.300 --> 40:27.900
I am your best friend.
–Oh, Alan!

40:28.100 --> 40:31.700
How can you possibly be
so selfish and cruel?

40:42.300 --> 40:43.500
Don't ruin it.

40:44.200 --> 40:46.900
–Oh, my God.
–See ya.

40:47.000 --> 40:50.300
What's your rush? Slow down.

40:50.500 --> 40:51.800
Treat her right.

40:55.000 --> 40:56.500
Romance her a little.

40:58.900 --> 41:00.000
At least…

41:00.600 --> 41:02.100
dance with her first.

41:02.500 --> 41:04.200
Dance?

41:06.100 --> 41:08.100
Hold her. Drink her in.

41:09.500 --> 41:10.700
Cherish her.

41:10.800 --> 41:11.500
♫ “L”

41:12.300 --> 41:16.900
♫ is for the way you look at me

41:17.000 --> 41:18.800
♫ “O” is for… ♫

41:18.900 --> 41:20.600
This is magic.

41:21.300 --> 41:22.500
It's fantastic.

41:24.000 --> 41:26.700
–God, are we weird?
–So weird.

